			<arg name="freq_high" optional="1" type="int/float" />
			<digest>
				Select a frequency range and report details to Outlet via the <m>select</m> tag
			</digest>
			<description>
				Syntax: <b>select <m>[&lt;int/float: freq_low&gt;]</m> <m>[&lt;int/float: freq_high&gt;]</m> </b><br />				<br />
				The <m>select</m> message takes two arguments: low selection frequency &amp; high selection frequency. Sending these commands to <o>spectrumdraw~</o> causes the requested selection to be displayed in the UI in the colour set by the <m>selectcolor</m> attribute. <br />
				It also causes selection information to be sent out of the object Outlet. The information reported to the Outlet consists of the symbol <m>select</m> followed by a list of numbers in the following order: <br />
				low freq / high freq / min freq / max freq / min amp / max amp / avg amp <br />
				Sending the symbol <m>select</m> alone (with no arguments) clears the selection. <br />
			</description>
